This paper discusses the use of a distributed database based on peer-to-peer network for high throughput computing systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of consensus algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions fault tolerance and scalability, which could place it in the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
